Brawijaya University: Brawijaya University (Indonesian: Universitas Brawijaya,[a] abbreviated as UB[b]), is an autonomous state university in Indonesia established on 5 January 1963, in Malang, East Java. Thu University of Brawijaya is recognized as one of the elite campuses in Indonesia and consistently ranked 5th in national level by official release from Kemenristekdikti along with University of Indonesia (UI), Bogor Agricultural University (IPB), Gadjah Mada University (UGM), and Bandung Institute of Technology (ITB).[6] In the International level, the University of Brawijaya is ranked 51st in Asia and 400th Worldwide, thus making it one of few Indonesian universities indexed by QS World University Rankings.[7][failed verification]
